    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> lamb mince</strong> and <strong>diced shallot</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the shallot has softened and the lamb has browned, then stir in 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1 min further</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<strong> beef stock mix</strong> in 100ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [120ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
