    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add a pot to a medium heat with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>[500ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> into the roux, a little at a time and cook for 4 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Add your<strong> grated cheese </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>– this is your<strong> cheese sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
